    <note>Ren(1) Bu [882] A fourth (5th by my count) generation descendant of a Later Tang prime minister, Huan [3425]. Hu Su drafted an edict appointing Ren(1) Gongzhi [3428] to an office, which identifies him as the grandson of Bu (CBD, 1, 662), but SS, 288.15a identifies Da [18254] and Yuan [18255] (generational indicator=radical 162) as Bu's sons. Bu must be Gongzhi's lineage granduncle from the Henan branch. The Wenyang branch probably refers to the Sichuan Ren. Huan was a Yaozhou, Sanyuan county resident (Shenxi). I am therefore making Zhongzheng [875] and his brothers, the 6th generation lineage kin of Ren(1) Huan, and identifying Bu as jia 'a,' and Zhongzheng, et. al. as jia 'b,' and probable lineage kin of Huan, Li [3429], as jia 'c.' XCB, 91.14a, 92.14a, 104.25b (n.), 110.14b, 116.2a, 6b; SS, 288.13b-14a. CBD, 1, 649.</note>
